parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Footwell Module and Junction Box Electronics)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of essential controls, including emergency flashers, turn signals, door locks, and windows, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

door locks and windows not functioning
security system and backup sensors not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Interior and Exterior Lights and Functions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of interior and exterior lights and functions can cause a safety hazard, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty passenger occupancy sensor mat can cause the passenger airbag to be disabled while in motion, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.

the airbag sensor warning and disabling of the airbag
warning light stays on continuously when the ignition is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag system failure can cause the airbag to deploy abruptly without warning, leading to injuries or accidents, or fail to deploy in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.

the airbag fails to deploy in the event of an accident.
